Spec: Plugin Build Script

Platform: Node.js

Purpose:
  Render source plugin templates into product plugin submodule outputs.

Owns:
  ./build.js
  ./plugins.js

Must:
  Render EJS templates from `../skills` into each `../../plugins/*/skills` output.
  Use `./plugins.js` as the explicit include map for product, shared, and skill files.
  Configure targets for Codex, Claude Code, GitHub Copilot, Junie, Cline, and Antigravity.
  Expose each target's human-readable agent name to EJS templates.
  Copy only files explicitly included by the target config into plugin outputs.
  Require every configured target to have a version in `../../plugin-versions.json`.
  Set each generated plugin manifest version from `../../plugin-versions.json` when the target config declares a manifest.
  Allow skill-only targets to omit a manifest by declaring `manifest: null`.
  Preserve each plugin submodule's `.git` directory during clean and build.
  Support build, check, and clean modes.
  Fail when generated output is stale in check mode.
  Log coarse build phases, target names, counts, and successful completion without per-file output.

Must not:
  Modify `../skills`, `../fragments`, `../plugins`, or `../shared`.
  Require network access during build.
